column5: A plane was reported missing after it's scheduled arrival time at Buttonville Airport did not happen. My condolences to the family but at least they have closure.   http://www.northumberlandnews.com/news/article/1353064--update-missing-plane-crashed-near-elizabethville
Thanks Ron...was trying to follow this story as I'm in Port Hope, my first thoughts was it mighta went down into rice from witness accounts.
Not what we wanted to hear, but it happens, in the sky and on the road, my condolences to the family.
Not good news. I used to ride my dirt bike in the Ganny when I was a crazy kid.
I thought you were talking about the crash of the russian superjet airlner on a sales pr tour. Guess they arent selling anymore now
